Tanatloc is a multi-physics FEA software for engineers and researchers.
Use the provided models for the most common problems, make your own, or partner with our experts to build one tailored to your needs.

Tanatloc is an FEA software based on FreeFEM, an extremely powerful and versatile open-source PDE solver. It runs locally using an electron build.

Case Study

DENSO

DENSO is a leading Japanese automotive and Fortune 500 company.
Hiroshi Ogawa, at DENSOs Heat Exchanger R&D Division, implemented a custom FreeFEM model on TANATLOC with the help of Professor Atsushi Suzuki from Osaka University.
DENSOs Solder Filling model was added to TANATLOC, and the calculations are deployed seamlessly on the cloud or on on-premise server via the ANCL Sharetask plug-in.
